---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PremiumClubCTA from '../components/PremiumClubCTA.astro';

// Cloudinary base for optimized images
const cdn = 'https://res.cloudinary.com/dhuc2wmhp/image/upload';
const opt = 'f_auto,q_auto';
---

<Layout
  title="Madrid Cannabis Guide 2026: Legal Rules & Tourist Safety"
  description="The Official 2026 Guide to Cannabis Rules in Madrid for Tourists. Learn about legal private clubs, street fines, tourist requirements, and how to avoid scams."
>
  <!-- Hero with background image -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero__bg">
      <img
        src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_1400/madrid-cannabis-guide/hero-madrid-gran-via.jpg`}
        alt="Madrid Gran Via at night"
        width="1400"
        height="800"
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="hero__content">
      <span class="badge">Updated for 2026</span>
      <h1>Madrid Cannabis Guide 2026: Legal Rules &amp; Tourist Safety</h1>
      <p>Everything tourists need to know about cannabis in Madrid &mdash; the law, the risks, and the only safe legal route through private social clubs.</p>
      <a
        href="https://www.weedmadrid.com/invite/vallehermoso-club-social-madrid"
        rel="sponsored noopener"
        target="_blank"
        class="hero__cta"
      >
        Get My Safe Club Invitation
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10m0 0L9 4m4 4L9 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </a>
      <div class="hero__social-proof" id="hero-social-proof">
        <span class="hero__social-proof-dot"></span>
        <span>8,400+ tourists used this guide in 2025</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">

    <!-- Section 1: Legal Rules -->
    <section id="legal" class="section">
      <div class="section__image">
        <img
          src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_800/madrid-cannabis-guide/spanish-congress-laws-v2.jpg`}
          alt="Spanish Congress building representing cannabis laws"
          width="800"
          height="420"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <h2>Is Weed Legal in Madrid? (The Private Club Loophole)</h2>

      <p>Spain does not have a single &ldquo;cannabis is legal&rdquo; law. Instead, the legal landscape is built on a constitutional distinction between <strong>private</strong> and <strong>public</strong> spaces. Understanding this distinction is the single most important thing for any tourist.</p>

      <h3>What the Law Actually Says</h3>
      <p>The Spanish Constitution protects the right to privacy in private spaces. Spanish courts have consistently ruled that personal cannabis consumption in a private setting is not a criminal offense. This legal grey area gave rise to <em>asociaciones cann&aacute;bicas</em> &mdash; private, members-only social clubs that operate as non-profit associations under Spain&rsquo;s freedom-of-association laws.</p>

      <p>These clubs do not &ldquo;sell&rdquo; cannabis. Legally, members collectively cultivate and share the harvest among themselves. This cooperative model is what keeps them operating within the boundaries of Spanish law.</p>

      <h3>What Remains Illegal &mdash; No Exceptions</h3>
      <div class="alert alert--danger">
        <strong>Always illegal in Madrid:</strong>
        Public consumption (streets, parks, plazas), any form of street purchase or sale, carrying cannabis in public spaces, growing cannabis without a private-club framework, and any sale for profit. These are not &ldquo;rarely enforced&rdquo; &mdash; police in tourist areas actively issue fines.
      </div>

      <p>The bottom line: cannabis in Madrid is only safe and legal when consumed inside a licensed private social club with a valid membership. Everywhere else, you are exposed to fines, scams, or both.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Street vs Clubs -->
    <section id="street-vs-clubs" class="section">
      <div class="section__image">
        <img
          src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_800/madrid-cannabis-guide/madrid-colorful-street.jpg`}
          alt="Colorful Madrid neighborhood street"
          width="800"
          height="420"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <h2>Street Fines vs. Safe Social Clubs</h2>

      <!-- PAS: Problem -->
      <p>Tourists often assume that Madrid works like Amsterdam, where coffee shops openly sell cannabis. <strong>It does not.</strong> The gap between street purchases and social clubs is enormous &mdash; legally, financially, and in terms of personal safety.</p>

      <!-- PAS: Agitate -->
      <h3>The Real Cost of Street Purchases</h3>
      <p>Spain&rsquo;s <strong>Citizen Safety Law</strong> (Ley Org&aacute;nica 4/2015, commonly called the <em>Ley Mordaza</em>) classifies public drug possession as a &ldquo;serious infraction.&rdquo; Fines range from <strong>&euro;601 to &euro;30,000</strong>, depending on the amount and circumstances. These are administrative fines, not criminal charges &mdash; but they are enforced on the spot and can ruin a holiday budget.</p>

      <p>Beyond fines, street purchases expose tourists to adulterated products. Madrid&rsquo;s municipal police have repeatedly warned that substances sold near Sol, Gran V&iacute;a, and Lavapies are frequently mixed with synthetic cannabinoids, herbs, or worse. There is zero quality control on the street.</p>

      <!-- PAS: Solution -->
      <h3>How Social Clubs Are Different</h3>
      <p>Licensed social clubs operate under municipal oversight. They source from controlled, traceable supply chains within their cooperative model. Members know what they are consuming &mdash; strain, potency, and origin. Clubs also provide a safe, private environment that fully complies with Spain&rsquo;s private-consumption legal framework.</p>

      <div class="comparison-box">
        <div class="comparison-box__col comparison-box__col--bad">
          <h4>Street Purchase</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>&euro;601&ndash;&euro;30,000 fines</li>
            <li>Adulterated products</li>
            <li>Zero legal protection</li>
            <li>Scam risk</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison-box__col comparison-box__col--good">
          <h4>Social Club</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>&euro;20&ndash;&euro;50 membership</li>
            <li>Lab-tested quality</li>
            <li>Fully legal &amp; private</li>
            <li>Safe environment</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <PremiumClubCTA variant="inline" />
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Tourist Requirements -->
    <section id="tourist-requirements" class="section">
      <div class="section__image">
        <img
          src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_800/madrid-cannabis-guide/friends-welcome-join-v2.jpg`}
          alt="Friends welcoming new member at social club"
          width="800"
          height="420"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <h2>Requirements for Tourists (ID, Age, Fees)</h2>

      <p>Legitimate cannabis social clubs in Madrid follow strict entry protocols. This is not red tape &mdash; it is the legal foundation that allows them to operate. If a club lets you walk in without these steps, it is not a legitimate club.</p>

      <h3>What You Need to Join</h3>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step__number">1</span>
          <div>
            <strong>A verified invitation</strong>
            <p>Spanish social clubs are private associations. You need an invitation from an existing member &mdash; a legal requirement, not a marketing gimmick.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step__number">2</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Valid photo ID</strong>
            <p>Passport for non-EU tourists, national ID for EU citizens. The club verifies and records your identity as required by Spanish association law.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step__number">3</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Minimum age of 21</strong>
            <p>Most Madrid clubs set the minimum at 21, though some accept 18+. Bring ID that clearly shows your date of birth.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step__number">4</span>
          <div>
            <strong>One-time membership fee</strong>
            <p>Between &euro;20 and &euro;50. This is a formal association membership, not a door charge. You&rsquo;ll receive a membership card.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Red Flags to Watch For</h3>
      <p>Any &ldquo;club&rdquo; that does not ask for ID, does not require an invitation, or lets you buy products without a membership is operating illegally. These are fronts that put you at legal risk. Legitimate clubs follow every step described above because their license depends on it.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Avoid Scams -->
    <section id="avoid-scams" class="section">
      <div class="section__image">
        <img
          src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_800/madrid-cannabis-guide/madrid-plaza-comparison.jpg`}
          alt="Madrid plaza where tourists are targeted by scams"
          width="800"
          height="420"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <h2>How to Avoid Tourist Scams in 2026</h2>

      <p>Madrid&rsquo;s cannabis scene has a well-documented scam ecosystem that specifically targets tourists. Knowing the patterns is your best defense.</p>

      <h3>The Street Dealer Approach</h3>
      <p>In areas like Sol, Gran V&iacute;a, Malasa&ntilde;a, and Chueca, individuals will approach tourists (especially at night) offering &ldquo;good weed&rdquo; or &ldquo;hash.&rdquo; In the best case, you get a low-quality, overpriced product and risk a &euro;601+ fine. In the worst case, the substance is synthetic or fake, and you have no recourse.</p>

      <h3>Fake &ldquo;Cannabis Clubs&rdquo;</h3>
      <p>Some unlicensed operations market themselves as cannabis clubs through flyers, cards left in hostels, or social media. They may have a physical location that looks like a club. But without a proper association license, municipal registration, and member governance, they are illegal dispensaries.</p>

      <h3>The WhatsApp/Telegram Delivery Scam</h3>
      <p>Promoted through stickers on lampposts and tourist-area posters, these &ldquo;delivery services&rdquo; ask for advance payment via Bizum or bank transfer, then either never deliver or deliver a fraudulent product. You have no legal protection because you are attempting an illegal purchase.</p>

      <div class="alert alert--danger">
        <strong>Simple rule:</strong>
        If someone approaches you unsolicited, if there&rsquo;s no ID check, or if you&rsquo;re asked to pay via messaging app &mdash; it&rsquo;s a scam. Every time.
      </div>

      <PremiumClubCTA variant="banner" />
    </section>

    <!-- Social Proof Lounge Image -->
    <section class="section section--lounge">
      <div class="section__image section__image--wide">
        <img
          src={`${cdn}/${opt},w_800/madrid-cannabis-guide/social-lounge-atmosphere.jpg`}
          alt="Social lounge with warm ambient lighting"
          width="800"
          height="400"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="section__image-overlay">
          <p class="section__image-quote">&ldquo;The club experience is nothing like the street. It&rsquo;s safe, legal, and surprisingly welcoming.&rdquo;</p>
          <span class="section__image-attr">&mdash; Sarah K., London &middot; Visited March 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section id="faq" class="section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <ul class="faq-list">
        <li class="faq-item">
          <p class="faq-question">Is cannabis legal in Madrid for tourists?</p>
          <p class="faq-answer">Cannabis is decriminalized for private use in Spain. Public consumption and purchase remain illegal with fines up to &euro;600. Tourists can legally consume cannabis only inside licensed private social clubs through a valid membership invitation. Street purchases are always illegal regardless of nationality.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="faq-item">
          <p class="faq-question">How can tourists access a cannabis social club in Madrid?</p>
          <p class="faq-answer">Tourists need a verified invitation from an existing member, a valid passport or EU ID proving they are 21+, and must pay a one-time membership fee (typically &euro;20&ndash;&euro;50). Walk-ins are not accepted at legitimate clubs. The invitation process exists because Spanish law only permits private, members-only associations.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="faq-item">
          <p class="faq-question">What are the fines for buying cannabis on the street in Madrid?</p>
          <p class="faq-answer">Buying or possessing cannabis in public spaces in Madrid carries administrative fines between &euro;601 and &euro;30,000 under Spain&rsquo;s Citizen Safety Law (Ley Mordaza). Street dealers often sell adulterated products and specifically target tourists. Police in tourist areas actively enforce these laws, especially around Sol, Gran V&iacute;a, and Malasa&ntilde;a.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    <section class="section section--final-cta">
      <h2>Ready to Visit a Safe, Legal Club?</h2>
      <p>Join thousands of tourists who chose the legal route. Get your verified invitation in under 3 minutes.</p>
      <a
        href="https://www.weedmadrid.com/invite/vallehermoso-club-social-madrid"
        rel="sponsored noopener"
        target="_blank"
        class="hero__cta"
      >
        Get My Verified Invitation
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10m0 0L9 4m4 4L9 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </a>
      <div class="hero__social-proof" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        <span class="hero__social-proof-dot"></span>
        <span id="personalized-cta-text">Trusted by tourists from 40+ countries</span>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <!-- Lightweight personalization script -->
  <script>
    (function() {
      // Returning visitor detection
      var visits = parseInt(localStorage.getItem('mcg_visits') || '0', 10);
      localStorage.setItem('mcg_visits', String(visits + 1));

      // Time-based personalization
      var hour = new Date().getHours();
      var greeting = '';
      if (hour < 12) greeting = 'Planning your Madrid trip this morning?';
      else if (hour < 18) greeting = 'Researching Madrid clubs this afternoon?';
      else greeting = 'Getting ready for a night out in Madrid?';

      // Update hero social proof for returning visitors
      var el = document.getElementById('hero-social-proof');
      if (el && visits > 0) {
        el.querySelector('span:last-child').textContent = 'Welcome back! ' + greeting + ' Your guide is ready.';
      }

      // Update final CTA for returning visitors
      var cta = document.getElementById('personalized-cta-text');
      if (cta && visits > 1) {
        cta.textContent = 'You\u2019ve visited ' + (visits + 1) + ' times. Ready to get your invitation?';
      }
    })();
  </script>
</Layout>